# Server Actions

This project uses **Next.js 16 App Router** with **JavaScript**. Read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before implementing unfamiliar APIs (see `AGENTS.md`).

## Default to Server Actions

For mutations, form submissions, and server-side data changes, use Server Actions — not client `fetch`, axios, or Route Handlers.

- Place actions in `src/actions/` (e.g. `src/actions/inquiry.js`) with `"use server"` at the top of the file
- Validate input with Zod in the action — see `zod-forms.mdc` (do not add a separate submission rule)
- Use Radix-wrapped fields from `src/components/` — see `radix-ui.mdc`
- Call from Server Components directly, or pass to Client Components as props

## Form wiring

**All form submissions** go through a Server Action on the `<form action={...}>` — never `onSubmit` + `fetch`.

```js
// src/actions/inquiry.js — validate with Zod (zod-forms.mdc), then persist
"use server";

export async function submitInquiry(prevState, formData) {
  // schema.safeParse(...), insert, revalidatePath, return { success, error, message }
}
```

```js
// Client form — useActionState for pending + feedback (ContactForm pattern)
"use client";

import { useActionState } from "react";
import { submitInquiry } from "@/actions/inquiry";

const [state, formAction, isPending] = useActionState(submitInquiry, initialState);

<form action={formAction}>...</form>
```

Server-only forms without pending UI may use `<form action={submitInquiry}>` directly.

## Avoid

- `fetch("/api/...")` from Client Components for mutations this app owns
- New `src/app/api/` routes when a Server Action suffices
- `"use client"` solely to POST data — keep the form server-rendered and action-driven when possible

## Reads

Prefer async Server Components for data fetching. Use Client Components only for interactivity that cannot live on the server.
